headline: GE Aerospace secures $5 billion U.S. Air Force contract
summary: The contract supports the U.S. government's foreign military sales program for F110-GE-129 engines, which power F-15 and F-16 fighter aircraft, the company said.  Earlier this month, the aerospace giant said it would invest nearly $1 billion in its U.S. factories and supply chain in 2025, in an effort to bolster its manufacturing process and enhance the implementation of new technologies and components.
